race.comment: COME ON GLAMOUR (8) showed good early dash and led for much of the way before weakening out of it when 5 lengths away in sixth over 1212m at Coffs Harbour. Will take some running down. EXTREME ALLY (9) is a six-year-old mare who is having her first run for the Beau Gorman stable. Resumes after lost rider at Kilmore at her last run three-and-a-half months ago. Fitter for a trial win at Ipswich and is in a nice race. Among the leading chances. BELISTIC MAN (1) missed the placings two runs back then didn't do any better last start when 8 lengths away in ninth over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. Capable of featuring prominently. COSMIC FORTUNE (7) was good fresh and shouldn't be far away.
